    {
      "id": "c6ef2f3e_d622bb13",
      "file_path": "adapters/mso-openstack-adapters/src/main/java/org/onap/so/heatbridge/HeatBridgeImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 484,
      "message": "I had no issue the using preconditions. I think you should do something like:\n\nAAIResultWrapper vserverWrapper = resourcesClient.get(vserverUri.depth(Depth.TWO));\nList<String> connectedPservers = vserverWrapper.getRelatedLinks(AAIObjectType.PSERVER)\nif (connectedPservers.size() == 1) {\n                 List<String> pciIds = HeatBridgeUtils.extractPciIdsFromVServer(vserverWrapper.asBean(Vserver.class));\n... etc ...\n\n}\nextractPciIdsFromVServer is a pretty expensive operation to throw away if you later find that you had more than pserver. You know the relationship state right away, it's better to check it then.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 97,
        "name": "Max Benjamin",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "max.benjamin@att.com",
        "username": "mfour"
      },
      "updated": "2019-11-08 15:41:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
